folder: Rapelye Street & Hicks Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Rapelye Street, north side, east from and including Hicks Street, showing St. Bernards R.C. Church and Rectory which are not designated in the Brooklyn Atlas of 1929. Also seen on Hicks Street is No. 651.

February 21, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Hicks Street & Rapelye Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Hicks Street, at the N.E. corner of Rapelye Street, showing St. Bernard's R.C. Church. Also seen is Rapelye Street, north side, east from Hicks Street.

August 5, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Hicks Street & Rapelye Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Hicks Street at Rapelye Street, Brooklyn.

P. L. Sperr, photographer
July 24, 1940
